ğŸ§  How the App Works

1.User enters input values on the website (e.g., hours studied)
2.JavaScript sends the data to Flask backend (/predict route)
3.predict.py loads model.joblib
4.ML model calculates predicted marks
5.Result is sent back and displayed on the webpage

â–¶ï¸ Running the Project Locally
1. Install Dependencies

Open terminal:
pip install flask numpy pandas scikit-learn joblib

2. Run the Flask Server
python app.py

3. Open the App
Go to:
http://127.0.0.1:5000

ğŸ“Š Model Training

The ML model is trained using data in marks.csv.

Training is handled by:
train.py

Run it if you want to retrain:
python train.py

This generates a new:
model.joblib

